commitResults.messageBody:
Methods dealing with storage like saving and loading are in Duke class.
Parsing of input from user and file to Task objects are handled by Task and
TaskManager class.

Common methods dealing with files and parsing of input should be abstracted
into their own classes. Having their own classes allows easier manipulation
through their respective public methods.

Let's extract all methods related to storage and parsing into a seperate class.

Minor renaming and refactoring are also included in this commit.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix ArrayOutOfBounds error in Parser
Update Duke to use Storage class
Add Command class
commitResults.messageBody:
Commands entered by User is parsed by main Duke class.

Extracting the various commands into a seperate Command class
will reduce spagetti code and provides the use of inheritance
for various command types.

Let's:
* Create A new class that represents the various actions that
are available to the user.

This will allow the use of polymorphism when executing commands.

* Note: only skeletal code is added for now, implementations
will follow in future commits.
* Parser for commands is also added.
* Main Duke class does not use Command class yet, will refactor
it to use Commands class once it is functional.
* Minor changes in Storage and Ui are also included in this commit.
